From fc572831b298fbb7c968148be6a9c3af57ca8239 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kol Crooks <kol.crooks@datadoghq.com>
Date: Mon, 4 May 2026 19:05:10 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Phase 7: Tour sub-mode (AI chapters with BYOK Anthropic key)

Adds a third sub-mode to the PR pane that generates an AI-narrated
review tour by calling api.anthropic.com directly with the user's
own API key. Key is encrypted via IEncryptionService (OS keychain)
before landing in IStorageService. Generated chapters cache by
{prId, headSha} so reopening doesn't re-bill.

Two presentation variants:
  - Chapters: rail of cards (title, summary, plus/minus counts,
    sensitive badge, mark-reviewed checkmark) with focused
    mini-diff detail.
  - Reading: prose layout with mini-diffs inline per chapter.

Settings live in the Command Palette for v1 (Configure key, Select
model, Toggle prompt caching). Tour empty state runs the configure
command directly via ICommandService.
